      <section id="id3261585">
        <title>[LO 4.6.2]</title>
        <para id="id2177488">Now you are ready to write an essay:</para>
        <para id="id3155914">Write about ‘<emphasis effect="italics">Reading as a hobby’</emphasis> in about 150 – 200 words (about 20 – 23 lines). </para>
        <para id="id3268495">You need to PLAN your essay using the ideas of your group.</para>
        <list id="id2610863" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Possible opening paragraph?</item>
        </list>
        <list id="id2363917" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Topics for different paragraphs</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id3059499">1.</para>
        <para id="id2885532">2.</para>
        <para id="id2897407">3.</para>
        <para id="id2847244">4.</para>
        <para id="id1966268">5.</para>
        <para id="id3146715">6.</para>
        <list id="id2119145" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Possible closing paragraph?</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id2062210">1. Consider using SOME figures of speech (alliteration, assonance, simile or metaphor)</para>
        <para id="id2393969">2. Make sure your spelling and your punctuation is correct.</para>
        <para id="id2330130">3.  Concentrate on writing as neatly as possible.</para>
        <para id="id2528848">4.  Go over the rough work, edit, check, revise, change where necessary</para>
        <para id="id3068448">NOW you are ready to write the neat essay:</para>
        <para id="id2054794">Give your essay a short, crisp, relevant title.</para>
        <para id="id2705201">Leave a line open between paragraphs.</para>
      </section>
